International Business Machines Corp Agreed To Settle Allegations-WSJ

Monday, 30 Sep 2013 12:34am EDT

The Wall Street Journal reported that International Business Machines Corp agreed to settle allegations some company online job listings expressed a preference for foreign workers with temporary visas over U.S. citizens, the Justice Department said. Under the terms of the settlement, IBM will pay $44,000 in civil penalties and revise its hiring and recruitment procedures to comply with the Immigration and Nationality Act. The Company will also provide reports to the government for two years.Â 

